More than 1,200 people celebrated the opening of a state-of-the-art church in Cardenas, Matanzas, Cuba on April 22. ⠀
The construction and inauguration of the church came as a result of many years of earnest prayer, and major efforts from Maranatha Volunteers International. The non-profit Adventist organization provides urgently needed churches and schools around the world. Each year, Maranatha not only raises awareness and funds for hundreds of projects but also mobilizes thousands of volunteers to construct the requested buildings. [photo: Maranatha Volunteers International]⠀
